Description: Fragment of neck and rising flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Red paint. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Production date: 203 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 32, 30 Name Theuphanes. Probably trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0747)
